<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Fattima:
[B]Well I still consider myself to be a somewhat "new" cleric as I am only level 31.  Up until I hit 15 or 16 I just took what I could get, which was mostly banded, cheap jewelry and some hand me downs that I didn't feel like selling from my main (at the time a 45ish ranger.)

Being that I am a dwarf, at 15 I started keeping my eyes open for Corflunk and Zarchoomi and asked all my friends to do the same.  By the time I hit 20 I had every piece of Bloodforge armor you can get except the BP.  IIRC I cheated and bought the leggings for like 30pp.

When I hit 25 I did the Ro armor quests with my Ranger, obtaining every piece except for the boots.  At that point the real twinking set in.  

I don't know if any of this helps, but I am now at 197 Wis, 199 if I pull out my old split paw hide gloves.  I wear all Ro armor except for some Donal's Vambs passed on to me by an guildie, eboots and a Skull Shaped Barbute (hey, I like the horny helm look on a dwarf.)  I used my ranger to twink me with about 3k pp, then I spent weeks in EC (the auction zone on our server) working that up to about 10k pp worth of gear.

As it stands, I can still upgrade a few slots relatively cheaply so I'm sure I'll hit 200 wis soon.  I love the look of the Ro armor and fully intend to wear it until I can start working on EM, then Thurg and eventually Skyshrine quest gear.
[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
