<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">trickstyle09</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I started a new halfing cleric recently.  I do not have any loot and was wondering where and at what levels I should camp gear at... Any suggestions would be appreciated.<P><BR>Thanks!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShinZed</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Assuming you're going untwinked, you'll be after patchwork / leather armour first, which is easily gotten.<P>Next step up from that is Banded at 10 when you have a bit of cash to spare (hopefully), which you hunt down a Smith for. Cost is about 1pp per AC on the piece. My advice is to skip bronze entirely.<P>Next on that at about level 20 - 30 is Virtue / Specialist armour (Bloodstained Tunic, PBB, Savant Cap etc). Specialist armour gives Wisdom, but tends to lack AC at the level you're getting it. Cleric Temple of Ro armour is big on AC but poor on Wisdom. Personally I prefer the Ro armour, your mileage may vary.<P>The Ro armour with a few obligatory specials (Adamantite Epaulets, Plat Jasper Rings, Handheld Wisdom Stuff etc) will last you to 50. From there it is up to you.<P>I personally wear what I loot, I don't buy anything except player made items.. therefore you might find better stuff available for yourself.<P>Melno Gredlong,<BR>36 Gnome Cleric,<BR>Xev</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Fattima</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well I still consider myself to be a somewhat "new" cleric as I am only level 31.  Up until I hit 15 or 16 I just took what I could get, which was mostly banded, cheap jewelry and some hand me downs that I didn't feel like selling from my main (at the time a 45ish ranger.)<P>Being that I am a dwarf, at 15 I started keeping my eyes open for Corflunk and Zarchoomi and asked all my friends to do the same.  By the time I hit 20 I had every piece of Bloodforge armor you can get except the BP.  IIRC I cheated and bought the leggings for like 30pp.<P>When I hit 25 I did the Ro armor quests with my Ranger, obtaining every piece except for the boots.  At that point the real twinking set in.  <P>I don't know if any of this helps, but I am now at 197 Wis, 199 if I pull out my old split paw hide gloves.  I wear all Ro armor except for some Donal's Vambs passed on to me by an guildie, eboots and a Skull Shaped Barbute (hey, I like the horny helm look on a dwarf.)  I used my ranger to twink me with about 3k pp, then I spent weeks in EC (the auction zone on our server) working that up to about 10k pp worth of gear.<P>As it stands, I can still upgrade a few slots relatively cheaply so I'm sure I'll hit 200 wis soon.  I love the look of the Ro armor and fully intend to wear it until I can start working on EM, then Thurg and eventually Skyshrine quest gear.<P>------------------<BR>&lt;a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22247"&gt;Fattima Faithhealer&lt;/a&gt; (The Magelo Profile still needs some updating)<BR>Level 31 Cleric in the service of Brell<BR>Spirit of the Moon<BR>Innoruuk Server</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
